SIMPLE: semi-diesel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semi-Diesel
<hw>Sem`i-Die"sel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designating an
internal-combustion engine of a type resembling the Diesel engine in
using as fuel heavy oil which is injected in a spray just before the end
of the compression stroke and is fired without electrical ignition. The
fuel is sprayed into an iron box (called a <xex>hot bulb</xex> or
<xex>hot pot</xex>) opening into the combustion chamber, and heated for
ignition by a blast-lamp until the engine is running, when it is,
ordinarily, kept red hot by the heat of combustion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semiditone</ent>⟦br⟧
